Touch.isTouching is not very useful during TouchPhase.ENDED, since it only tells us if we were touching the object during TouchPhase.BEGAN. Touch should include a method to see if we are _still_ touching an object.

Say we are talking about a button. We want the user to be able to change their mind about a button press by sliding their cursor/finger off of the button before they release it. To this end, we should check if the cursor is still touching the button when TouchPhase.ENDED fires.

```
 public function isStillTouching(target:DisplayObject):Boolean 
 { 
    if (target.hitTest(this.getLocation(target)) {
        return true;
    }
    return false;
 } 
```

